      public JvmAnnotation.Builder<T> addClass(String name, JvmTypeOrVoid value)
      Adds class value to the annotation being built. The value must be
      • JvmClassType if it represents ordinary class,
      • JvmArrayType if it represents array class,
      • JvmPrimitiveType if it represents primitive class,
      • JvmVoid if it represents void.class.

      public JvmAnnotation.ArrayBuilder<JvmAnnotation.Builder<T>,JvmTypeOrVoid> startClasses(String name)
      Starts building an array of class values. The values added to the array must be JvmClassOrArrayType, JvmPrimitiveType or JvmVoid. The array is not added to this builder until JvmAnnotation.ArrayBuilder.end() is called on the returned builder.

    • startAnnotation
